cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a new architecture for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for action recognition, which falls under the computer vision (CV) domain. The proposed architecture involves introducing controlled non-linearities in the form of interactions between delayed input samples of data, which is related to machine learning (ML) and neural networks (NNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV. 

The paper also focuses on reducing the number of parameters required for the same classification task as a conventional NN, which is related to optimization and neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper proposes a sophisticated adaptation of the network to nonlinearly fuse spatial and temporal information of a video sequence, which is related to multimedia (MM) and computer vision. Therefore, cs.MM is also a likely sub-category.
